3 hours ago, RainDreamer said:

A few things:

1. Please follow the correct error report/ revert procedure so everyone know what happened, I will do one:

  Hide contents

 

The progress before the error

This is the error that has been made by legoclone09, violating rule 4 due to representing the current number incorrectly, omitting the minus sign:

And Dfthu, while seemingly understand it is -1, continues on without correcting the error:

Thus, the game will be reverted to Mycrof's post at -2.

 

Error report should at least somewhat following the procedures in the OP under rule 6. The 3 most important things we GM need to know is: 1. What rule has been broken? 2.What was the progress before the error? 3.What happened after the error? so try to cover them in when reverting to ensure there is no dispute.

2. I still see some edits being made. Please really, really try not to edit your post, even if it is wrong and you didn't meant what you post, since that complicates things for us when checking stuff. Be careful with your post.

3. Replying to:

Have fun with managing the game over there!

1 hour ago, Dman979 said:

Be careful, @PB666; your team is making it's fair share of mistakes, too!

Do they explicitly have to state the sign, if the direction is negative? @RainDreamer

I think we are well below the pairing rule. Yep, folks, the rules have apparently changed, you must explicitly state your operation , either something indication minus, (-), down, ect. 

Previously you only needed a number now you need a direction also, so it would seem. 

Quote

Player 8 post: "5" This is no longer acceptable, as the rule now require players to also explicitly declare the operation they did to the number. Even though it can be deducted from previous post, the post deviate from the requirement and can be used as ground for reversal.

Thanks for the heads up. @Dman979

The previous valid value of mine was 4. The GMs have made this game tough so we have to stay on our toes. 

Heads up to GMs " Even though it can be deducted from previous post " should be "Even though it can be deduced from the previous post"
